        {
            "parameters": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": "https://api.deepseek.com/chat/completions",
                "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
                "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
                "sendBody": true,
                "options": {},
                "specifyBody": "json",
                "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"deepseek-chat\",\n  \"temperature\": 0.1,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"system\",\n      \"content\": \"Tu es un analyste SDR charge de classifier la reponse d\u0027un prospect a un email de prospection. Tu dois produire STRICTEMENT un JSON valide avec les cles exactes: intention, niveau_interet, resume, propose_creneau, creneau_brut, action_index. Regles: intention est une courte etiquette parmi interesse, question, refus, desabonnement, demande_creneau, autre. niveau_interet est exactement chaud, tiede ou froid. resume fait 1 a 3 phrases courtes. propose_creneau est un booleen. creneau_brut contient le texte du creneau si present sinon null. action_index doit etre: 0 si le prospect est interesse ou demande des creneaux, 1 si le prospect veut se desabonner ou refuse tout contact, 2 si c\u0027est un refus commercial clair, 3 pour une question ou reponse generale necessitant une reponse. Si tu hesites, choisis 3.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"={{ JSON.stringify({ prospect: $(\u0027PostgreSQL Identifier Prospect Repondant\u0027).first().json, email_recu: { from: $(\u0027Gmail Trigger Reponses\u0027).first().json.from || \u0027\u0027, subject: $(\u0027Gmail Trigger Reponses\u0027).first().json.subject || \u0027\u0027, text: $(\u0027Gmail Trigger Reponses\u0027).first().json.text || $(\u0027Gmail Trigger Reponses\u0027).first().json.snippet || \u0027\u0027 } }) }}\"\n    }\n  ]\n}"
            },
            "id": "99c62cc3-a7fc-4476-b264-8a17a21aa163",
            "name": "DeepSeek Analyser Reponse",
            "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
            "typeVersion": 4.2,
            "position": [
                -752,
                112
            ],
            "credentials": {
                "httpHeaderAuth": {
                    "id": "Fi7piKShxfsxAA0V",
                    "name": "Header Auth agent_s"
                }
            }
        },
        {
            "parameters": {
                "jsCode": "const response = $input.first().json || {};\nconst content = response?.choices?.[0]?.message?.content || \u0027\u0027;\nconst prospect = $(\u0027PostgreSQL Identifier Prospect Repondant\u0027).first().json || {};\nconst gmailData = $(\u0027Gmail Trigger Reponses\u0027).first().json || {};\n\nlet analyse;\nlet analyse_source = \u0027deepseek\u0027;\ntry {\n  const clean = String(content).replace(/```json|```/g, \u0027\u0027).trim();\n  analyse = JSON.parse(clean);\n} catch (e) {\n  analyse = {};\n  analyse_source = \u0027fallback\u0027;\n}\n\nconst normalizeText = (value, fallback = \u0027\u0027) =\u003e typeof value === \u0027string\u0027 ? value.trim() || fallback : fallback;\nconst normalizeAction = (value) =\u003e Number.isInteger(value) ? value : Number.parseInt(value, 10);\nconst actionIndexRaw = normalizeAction(analyse.action_index);\nconst actionIndex = [0, 1, 2, 3].includes(actionIndexRaw) ? actionIndexRaw : 3;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    ...prospect,\n    intention: normalizeText(analyse.intention, \u0027question\u0027),\n    niveau_interet: [\u0027chaud\u0027, \u0027tiede\u0027, \u0027froid\u0027].includes(analyse.niveau_interet) ? analyse.niveau_interet : \u0027tiede\u0027,\n    resume: normalizeText(analyse.resume, \u0027Analyse indisponible\u0027),\n    propose_creneau: Boolean(analyse.propose_creneau),\n    creneau_brut: normalizeText(analyse.creneau_brut, \u0027\u0027),\n    action_index: actionIndex,\n    analyse_source,\n    gmail_message_id: gmailData.id || \u0027\u0027,\n    gmail_thread_id: gmailData.threadId || \u0027\u0027,\n    corps_reponse: normalizeText((gmailData.text || gmailData.snippet || \u0027\u0027).substring(0, 1000), \u0027\u0027),\n    objet_reponse: normalizeText(gmailData.subject, \u0027\u0027)\n  }\n}];"
            },
